- TRAINEE: Should we take this tissue for now?
- TRAINEE: Okay.

1115
00:51:17,824 --> 00:51:19,766
(But distracted by the mention of tissue)
TRAINEE: Because it was in the drawer, right?

1116
00:51:23,966 --> 00:51:25,700
(Meanwhile, Class '10)

1117
00:51:26,266 --> 00:51:28,033
DANIEL: Hey, this is a drawer too!

1118
00:51:28,033 --> 00:51:30,000
HAMIN: But this is the only thing
of mine in this drawer.

1119
00:51:31,600 --> 00:51:32,700
HAMIN: This couldn't be it.

1120
00:51:33,216 --> 00:51:34,560
DANIEL: Hey, this is it!

1121
00:51:34,560 --> 00:51:35,170
HAMIN: Is this it?

1122
00:51:35,232 --> 00:51:37,728
(Why did I think it wasn't?)
DANIEL: Yeah, it's this, hurry up, hurry.

1123
00:51:37,728 --> 00:51:40,128
HAMIN: Everyone, come here!

1124
00:51:40,128 --> 00:51:41,344
(What on earth is that?)
TRAINEE: What was it?

1125
00:51:43,520 --> 00:51:44,866
DANIEL: You fool, why this?

1126
00:51:44,866 --> 00:51:46,066
HAMIN: Oh, really?

1127
00:51:46,066 --> 00:51:47,300
HAMIN: I thought the staff misplaced it!

1128
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:49,300
JAEWON: I was watching this the whole time!

1129
00:51:49,500 --> 00:51:50,933
(Witnesses everywhere)
TRAINEE: I was watching it too.

1130
00:51:51,151 --> 00:51:52,032
DANIEL: Then why didn't you take it?

1131
00:51:52,032 --> 00:51:54,433
(Only DANIEL seems to know what the item is)
JAEWON: I thought someone forgot to take it.

1132
00:51:55,633 --> 00:51:56,466
(Wrong answer)
DANIEL: Walkie-talkie?

1133
00:51:56,466 --> 00:51:58,900
(Wrong again)
DANIEL: Recorder! Recorder!

1134
00:51:58,900 --> 00:51:59,766
STAFF: Recorder?

1135
00:51:59,766 --> 00:52:01,568
(Class '10 thought it was filming equipment)
JAEWON: Oh, I thought this was something we actually use.

1136
00:52:01,568 --> 00:52:02,837
TRAINEE: Come on, no, no.

1137
00:52:03,008 --> 00:52:03,680
(Come out!)
TRAINEE: It's wrong!

1138
00:52:03,680 --> 00:52:05,184
JAEWON: No, it's right, we're right.

1139
00:52:05,633 --> 00:52:06,656
STAFF: What do you think it is?

1140
00:52:06,656 --> 00:52:07,712
TRAINEE: I think it's a recorder.

1141
00:52:08,544 --> 00:52:09,920
(Another wrong answer)
TRAINEE: A cassette! Ah!

1142
00:52:10,528 --> 00:52:11,392
CHARLIE: A cassette?

1143
00:52:11,733 --> 00:52:14,033
(No matter how you look at it...)
TRAINEE: Model, Bravo Plus.

1144
00:52:14,900 --> 00:52:16,900
JAEWON: I don't know what this is.

1145
00:52:17,800 --> 00:52:20,566
STAFF: Class '10 has brought an unidentified object.

1146
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:22,733
DANIEL: What is this? This can't be it.

1147
00:52:22,733 --> 00:52:23,633
(Tissue)

1148
00:52:23,680 --> 00:52:24,896
HANBI: I don't think so either.

1149
00:52:24,896 --> 00:52:26,433
DANIEL: Absolutely not, no way!

1150
00:52:26,433 --> 00:52:27,616
(Opponent refuses)
DANIEL: Just go away.

1151
00:52:28,400 --> 00:52:29,833
SONGHA: But you never know!

1152
00:52:30,300 --> 00:52:31,633
STAFF: The result is...

1153
00:52:31,633 --> 00:52:32,900
STAFF: Class '10 is correct.

1154
00:52:32,900 --> 00:52:34,233
- STAFF: Class '10 is correct.
- ALL: Wow!!

1155
00:52:34,666 --> 00:52:36,133
(Ultrasonic screams)

1156
00:52:37,533 --> 00:52:38,900
STAFF: Then let me explain

1157
00:52:39,500 --> 00:52:42,528
(The identity of the mysterious item)
STAFF: the items that Class '10 brought.

1158
00:52:43,000 --> 00:52:44,566
(What on earth is this)
(What is this?)

1159
00:52:45,033 --> 00:52:47,400
(This item, with diverse shapes and colors)

1160
00:52:47,500 --> 00:52:49,400
(You must be the last person
on earth still using a pager.)

1161
00:52:50,066 --> 00:52:51,266
(Beep!)

1162
00:52:51,266 --> 00:52:52,600
(I have heard about it)
JAEWON: A pager!

1163
00:52:52,600 --> 00:52:54,200
HAMIN: Is this a pager?

1164
00:52:54,200 --> 00:52:55,533
DANIEL: Ah, is this a beeper?

1165
00:52:55,533 --> 00:52:58,800
STAFF: They saw the pager,
but didn't recognize it, so they put it back.

1166
00:52:59,200 --> 00:53:00,666
(If we had known)
DANIEL: We could've been first.

1167
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:02,166
(Too bad)
JAEWON: I watched it from the start.

1168
00:53:02,166 --> 00:53:04,733
(Class '00 A.U.I is searching for the remaining answer)
JAEWON: We'll find it, we'll find it.

1169
00:53:04,928 --> 00:53:05,633
(Found it)
TRAINEE: This is it!

1170
00:53:06,100 --> 00:53:08,233
HYUNJUN: "Don't distinguish between daughters
and sons, Have one child and raise them well."

1171
00:53:08,233 --> 00:53:10,533
HYUNJUN: There was no such slogan in the 2000s.

1172
00:53:10,800 --> 00:53:11,766
HYUNJUN: This is...

1173
00:53:11,866 --> 00:53:13,233
HYUNJUN: This is totally the one in '90s!

1174
00:53:13,700 --> 00:53:15,600
NICHOLAS: It's encouraging higher birth rates there.

1175
00:53:16,200 --> 00:53:18,466
(There's even a poster
saying the opposite of the slogan!)

1176
00:53:19,033 --> 00:53:21,933
(Giving 10 points to Class '00)
STAFF: We'll give points to the class

1177
00:53:21,933 --> 00:53:22,866
(who scored third)
STAFF: that answered correctly in third place.

1178
00:53:23,133 --> 00:53:24,000
HANBI: 10 points are still something!

1179
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:26,300
HANBI: It's okay, it's okay, we can still win!

1180
00:53:26,560 --> 00:53:30,752
(Final score, A.U.I 50 points, WONHA~JANNI
30 points, Five Boys Over Flowers 10 points)

1181
00:53:31,933 --> 00:53:33,100
(Class '90 in first place)
JUSTIN: Well done, we did well!

1182
00:53:33,100 --> 00:53:34,033
(Class '90 in first place)
NICHOLAS: Good job, good job!

1183
00:53:34,033 --> 00:53:35,456
(Proud)
TRAINEE: We got 50 points.

1184
00:53:36,466 --> 00:53:38,833
JAEWON: When's lunch time?

1185
00:53:39,400 --> 00:53:42,233
- SONGHA: Do you know today's lunch menu?
- TRAINEE: No, I don't.

1186
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:45,033
(As everyone grows hungry)

1187
00:53:46,600 --> 00:53:48,400
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: Attention from the faculty office.)

1188
00:53:48,600 --> 00:53:50,833
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: We will now begin lunch time.)

1189
00:53:51,300 --> 00:53:53,933
(Finally, time to eat)
(TEACHERS' OFFICE: Enjoy your delicious lunch.)

1190
00:53:54,266 --> 00:53:55,351
JUSTIN: Hey, why is it so big?

1191
00:53:56,906 --> 00:53:58,138
NICHOLAS: Wow, it's really big.

1192
00:53:58,866 --> 00:53:59,872
(This one's massive too)

1193
00:53:59,936 --> 00:54:00,760
TRAINEE: It's barley tea.

1194
00:54:00,800 --> 00:54:02,496
(Always hanging next to the desk back then)
TRAINEE: Wow, sesame oil.

1195
00:54:02,496 --> 00:54:03,518
TRAINEE: Yes.

1196
00:54:04,128 --> 00:54:06,560
('90s lunch box)
TRAINEE: What's this?

1197
00:54:07,680 --> 00:54:08,256
TRAINEE: Rice.

1198
00:54:08,256 --> 00:54:09,120
TRAINEE: It's seaweed soup!

1199
00:54:09,120 --> 00:54:11,133
(Warm rice and soup kept hot in a thermos)

1200
00:54:11,392 --> 00:54:12,672
(Stir-fried fish cakes and soy-braised quail eggs)
TRAINEE: Quail egg, fish cake.

1201
00:54:14,966 --> 00:54:17,033
(Students' all-time favorite side dish sausage)
TRAINEE: There really is sausage.

1202
00:54:17,333 --> 00:54:18,766
(Sweet black beans, good for your brain)

1203
00:54:19,328 --> 00:54:21,088
(Rolled omelet, a must in your lunch box)
TRAINEE: Egg. There's egg, rolled omelet!

1204
00:54:21,088 --> 00:54:21,984
TRAINEE: It looks really delicious.

1205
00:54:22,176 --> 00:54:23,680
(A lunch box full of care and memories)
TRAINEE: Honestly, mom's cooking is always the best.

1206
00:54:23,808 --> 00:54:25,984
TRAINEE: It's really delicious.

1207
00:54:26,560 --> 00:54:28,416
(Let's eat by joining our desks)
TRAINEE: Hey, let's join them and eat.

1208
00:54:29,216 --> 00:54:32,640
ALL: Thank you for the meal.

1209
00:54:33,600 --> 00:54:34,784
TRAINEE: Mom's cooking is the best.

1210
00:54:37,900 --> 00:54:39,633
(A bite of hot rice first)

1211
00:54:43,900 --> 00:54:45,966
(Try it soaked in the soup)

1212
00:54:48,366 --> 00:54:49,933
(Eating all the side dishes evenly)

1213
00:54:50,700 --> 00:54:53,400
(Drinking straight from the thermos)

1214
00:54:53,400 --> 00:54:54,349
HYUNJUN: Kimchi, kimchi!

1215
00:54:55,328 --> 00:54:56,352
WOOLIN: Eat a lot.

1216
00:54:57,376 --> 00:55:00,266
HYUNJUN: WOOLIN, I'll give my meat for you.

1217
00:55:03,136 --> 00:55:05,466
JUSTIN: KASSHO, I'll give you
a bite of my rolled omelet.

1218
00:55:06,200 --> 00:55:08,100
(When there were no separate
side dishes for you and me)

1219
00:55:08,400 --> 00:55:10,700
(Sausage side dish, yum!)

1220
00:55:12,233 --> 00:55:15,133
(Focusing only on the sausages)

1221
00:55:15,766 --> 00:55:19,366
(Sneaking a glance at HYUNJUN's lunch box)

1222
00:55:20,033 --> 00:55:23,800
(Stealing sausage while he isn't looking)

1223
00:55:24,800 --> 00:55:26,766
(Every class had a kid like this)

1224
00:55:28,433 --> 00:55:29,632
(Playing dumb)

1225
00:55:29,632 --> 00:55:30,880
TRAINEE: Let's go eat.

1226
00:55:31,328 --> 00:55:32,096
TRAINEE: Let's go!

1227
00:55:32,333 --> 00:55:33,856
(Where are Class '10 heading?)

1228
00:55:33,856 --> 00:55:35,200
TRAINEE: Wow, what's this?

1229
00:55:35,200 --> 00:55:36,448
TRAINEE: Where is this?

1230
00:55:36,576 --> 00:55:37,216
TRAINEE: Hey!

1231
00:55:37,216 --> 00:55:38,304
TRAINEE: Wow, this is it.

1232
00:55:40,412 --> 00:55:41,440
(Cafeteria)
TRAINEE: We've got a cafeteria.

1233
00:55:41,632 --> 00:55:43,233
(State-of-the-art cafeteria in 2010s)
TRAINEE: We've got a cafeteria.

1234
00:55:43,264 --> 00:55:45,066
(From the 3rd-floor classroom)
TRAINEE: Are you jealous?

1235
00:55:45,066 --> 00:55:47,900
(Going down from the 3rd-floor
classroom to the 2nd floor)

1236
00:55:48,866 --> 00:55:50,966
(Spacious and pleasant dining area)

1237
00:55:50,966 --> 00:55:51,712
(Eating from shiny metal trays)
TRAINEE: What's this?

1238
00:55:51,712 --> 00:55:54,048
TRAINEE: It's been a while since school tray meals.

1239
00:55:54,048 --> 00:55:55,840
(Balanced meal on a shining tray)

1240
00:55:55,840 --> 00:55:56,544
TRAINEE: Looks delicious.

1241
00:55:57,433 --> 00:55:59,520
(Today's cafeteria main dish, pork cutlet)

1242
00:55:59,648 --> 00:56:01,632
TRAINEE: Oh, it really looks tasty.

1243
00:56:04,096 --> 00:56:05,184
(Cafeteria)

1244
00:56:06,368 --> 00:56:09,600
JAEWON: I should eat a lot.

1245
00:56:09,856 --> 00:56:10,976
JAEWON: I was hungry.

1246
00:56:11,008 --> 00:56:14,688
JAEWON: Gotta serve it
like a real cafeteria, lots of rice.

1247
00:56:15,100 --> 00:56:16,666
(Loaded with curry)

1248
00:56:16,666 --> 00:56:17,900
(Loaded with curry, loaded with pork cutlet)

1249
00:56:19,488 --> 00:56:22,784
(Having a hearty appetite,
loaded with seaweed soup too)

1250
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:25,366
DANIEL: I'm really curious how much HAMIN will eat.

1251
00:56:25,366 --> 00:56:28,300
(Famous big eater)
HAMIN: I had breakfast, so I won't eat much.

1252
00:56:29,120 --> 00:56:31,392
(Food expert)
HAMIN: The round part of the pork cutlet is the tastiest.

1253
00:56:32,608 --> 00:56:33,410
HAMIN: Wow, seaweed soup.

1254
00:56:34,624 --> 00:56:35,744
(How much are you taking?)
HARUTA: Hurry up!

1255
00:56:37,408 --> 00:56:39,680
(The person who said he wouldn't eat much)

1256
00:56:39,966 --> 00:56:41,433
(Piled high)
TRAINEE: Even just looking now...

1257
00:56:42,240 --> 00:56:44,300
- JAEWON: It's a mountain from here.
- TRAINEE: It's piled rice, piled rice.

1258
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:46,528
(Filled)
TRAINEE: Didn't you eat earlier?

1259
00:56:48,066 --> 00:56:49,800
HAMIN: I'm not eating a lot.

1260
00:56:50,266 --> 00:56:52,500
(Even HAMIN, who eats little, finishes all the serving)

1261
00:56:52,544 --> 00:56:54,933
(2000s)
TRAINEE: Here we go, here we go.

1262
00:56:55,264 --> 00:56:56,466
(An unusually excited-looking back view)

1263
00:56:57,152 --> 00:56:58,624
(Peek 1, Peek 2)
TRAINEE: You know we have to go this way, right?

1264
00:57:00,466 --> 00:57:01,952
KACHIN: Wow!

1265
00:57:02,166 --> 00:57:04,100
(Symbol of lunch hour in the '00s)
TRAINEE: Oh yeah, the lunch cart!

1266
00:57:04,366 --> 00:57:06,624
(Before the cafeteria? Lunch cart!)
TRAINEE: Wow, this nostalgia.

1267
00:57:06,944 --> 00:57:08,480
TRAINEE: Amazing.

1268
00:57:08,640 --> 00:57:11,616
(Nostalgia of class helpers serving food)
TRAINEE: One lunch helper served everyone, right?

1269
00:57:13,866 --> 00:57:16,256
(Same menu as Class '10's cafeteria)
TRAINEE: Wow, pork cutlet!

1270
00:57:16,256 --> 00:57:17,155
TRAINEE: Cabbage salad.

1271
00:57:17,280 --> 00:57:18,080
TRAINEE: Wow, today's lunch is

1272
00:57:18,080 --> 00:57:20,500
(A heartwarming lunch meal)
TRAINEE: amazing, today's lunch is amazing.

1273
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:22,848
- HANBI: Alright, I'll be today's lunch helper.
- TRAINEE: Oh, that's cool.

1274
00:57:22,848 --> 00:57:25,504
(Today's lunch helper: HANBI)
HANBI: Guys, do you want to bring the lunch trays?

1275
00:57:26,266 --> 00:57:30,266
SONGHA: There's usually someone
who distributes this every day.

1276
00:57:30,770 --> 00:57:31,680
TRAINEE: Chef.

1277
00:57:31,904 --> 00:57:33,433
HANBI: When one person passes by like this?

1278
00:57:33,433 --> 00:57:35,800
(Explaining the lunch cart to classmates from abroad)
HANBI: Line up like this and get served one by one.

1279
00:57:36,864 --> 00:57:37,536
HANBI: SADAHARU, how much?

1280
00:57:37,536 --> 00:57:38,464
SADAHARU: Give me a lot, please.

1281
00:57:38,602 --> 00:57:39,533
- HANBI: A lot? SADAHARU, a lot?
- SADAHARU: Please give me really a lot.

1282
00:57:39,533 --> 00:57:41,373
(The rule when receiving lunch: Giving a lot)
HANBI: I'll really give you a lot.

1283
00:57:41,373 --> 00:57:42,066
SADAHARU: Yes, I'm so hungry.

1284
00:57:42,400 --> 00:57:43,776
SADAHARU: With lots of love.

1285
00:57:43,776 --> 00:57:44,896
- HANBI: My affection.
- SADAHARU: Yes.

1286
00:57:45,033 --> 00:57:47,200
- HANBI: I'll pile it up with all my love.
- SADAHARU: Thank you.

1287
00:57:48,166 --> 00:57:49,033
(A tower of love)
SADAHARU: Oh, that's too much.

1288
00:57:49,800 --> 00:57:52,700
(Today's generous lunch helper)
HANBI: There's only five of us.

1289
00:57:53,664 --> 00:57:55,136
KACHIN: Eat a lot.

1290
00:57:55,296 --> 00:57:56,320
TRAINEE: I'll eat a lot.

1291
00:57:56,320 --> 00:57:57,248
KACHIN: That's good.

1292
00:57:58,300 --> 00:58:01,433
(Waiting for insert shot for a moment)

1293
00:58:01,632 --> 00:58:04,608
(Eyes fixed on the tray)

1294
00:58:05,824 --> 00:58:06,848
SADAHARU: Ah, looks delicious.

1295
00:58:09,340 --> 00:58:11,872
(SADAHARU can't take his eyes off the tray)

1296
00:58:12,766 --> 00:58:15,700
(Wait)

1297
00:58:16,282 --> 00:58:17,856
(Haha)

1298
00:58:18,163 --> 00:58:19,872
TRAINEE: Is everyone hungry?

1299
00:58:20,092 --> 00:58:23,136
SADAHARU: Hungry.

1300
00:58:23,136 --> 00:58:24,480
(Unfamiliar waiting)

1301
00:58:25,200 --> 00:58:27,200
(Meanwhile, TATA was looking around)

1302
00:58:27,392 --> 00:58:29,440
TATA: It looks so ugly, wait...

1303
00:58:30,700 --> 00:58:33,533
(Looks around once more)
TATA: Hold on...

1304
00:58:34,833 --> 00:58:38,300
(Rearranging cherry tomatoes one by one)

1305
00:58:38,816 --> 00:58:41,568
(Even pushing the pork cutlet aside)

1306
00:58:42,672 --> 00:58:44,672
(Only then does he leave, satisfied)

1307
00:58:45,344 --> 00:58:46,867
(Five Boys Over Flowers)
ALL: Thank you for the meal!

1308
00:58:47,933 --> 00:58:49,833
HANBI: It's been so long since I've had school lunch.

1309
00:58:51,700 --> 00:58:53,933
(The flavor hits immediately)

1310
00:58:54,700 --> 00:58:57,200
(SADAHARU starts with the pork cutlet)

1311
00:58:57,600 --> 00:59:01,400
SONGHA: Have you ever eaten from a tray like this?

1312
00:59:02,112 --> 00:59:03,136
(Shaking his head)
SADAHARU: No, I haven't.

1313
00:59:03,466 --> 00:59:06,066
(As expected)
SONGHA: He put the seaweed soup over there.

1314
00:59:06,400 --> 00:59:07,680
(All by itself)

1315
00:59:08,192 --> 00:59:10,912
(Seaweed soup brought like sauce)
- SADAHARU: Here's the soup. - TRAINEE: Who eats soup like that?

1316
00:59:12,200 --> 00:59:13,466
(Slurp)

1317
00:59:14,133 --> 00:59:16,666
(Anyway, eating well)
SADAHARU: It's delicious.

1318
00:59:16,866 --> 00:59:20,433
TATA: I don't have soup. There was no space.

1319
00:59:20,608 --> 00:59:22,912
(TATA, who's more into pork cutlet)

1320
00:59:23,456 --> 00:59:26,200
(Taking a bite of rice)

1321
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:28,966
(Taking a bite of rice,
and then immediately pork cutlet)

1322
00:59:29,533 --> 00:59:31,166
(This time, pile up kimchi, rice and pork cutlet well)

1323
00:59:31,433 --> 00:59:33,833
(A hearty bite)

1324
00:59:34,812 --> 00:59:35,904
(In a state of trance)

1325
00:59:36,448 --> 00:59:37,344
(Glance)

1326
00:59:37,920 --> 00:59:40,666
(Humming while taking SADAHARU's food)
SADAHARU: Eat, eat, eat.

1327
00:59:42,533 --> 00:59:45,400
(Prime eating-and-growing age)

1328
00:59:45,500 --> 00:59:47,366
- TATA: It's so delicious.
- SONGHA: Is it delicious?

1329
00:59:47,800 --> 00:59:48,704
(Awesome)
SONGHA: Eat a lot.

1330
00:59:49,066 --> 00:59:52,233
HANBI: Don't you have that?
The sleepiness after eating school lunch?

1331
00:59:52,303 --> 00:59:54,464
SADAHARU: All the time.

